alerts.description: ...CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS TODAY... .Despite much cooler temperatures, very strong and gusty northwest winds combined with low relative humidity will again produce extreme fire danger on the plains. Wind gusts are currently gusting in the 40 to 55 mph range across much of the plains. Humidities are currently in the 18 to 25 percent range and will continue to drop this afternoon. The strongest winds will occur generally east of a Greeley to Denver line and extend towards Limon. Gusts up to 60 mph will be possible late morning through the afternoon. Red Flag Warning remains in effect for all of the plains of Colorado. ...RED FLAG WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MST THIS EVENING FOR WIND AND LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY FOR THE I-25 CORRIDOR INTO THE PALMER DIVIDE... * Affected Area...Fire Weather Zones 239...240...241 and 247. * Timing...Late this morning through this afternoon. * Winds...Northwest 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph. * Relative Humidity...As low as 10 percent. * Impacts...Conditions will be favorable for new fire starts and rapid growth of fires. Outdoor burning is prohibited.
